text:
Argentina soccer legend Diego Maradona has died after suffering a cardiac arrest at age 60, his lawyer says.

Regarded as one of the greatest players in the game's history, he became a household name after inspiring his country to World Cup glory in 1986. https://t.co/wKhQpbj5PW

text: A giant study of more than 12,000 mutations in the novel coronavirus finds none of them has made a big difference in how easily it infects people, researchers have reported https://t.co/AyzO1aWPPm

text:
Four years ago, a stranger was accidentally invited to Thanksgiving dinner via text message.

Wanda Dench and Jamal Hinton celebrated once again in Arizona, but there was an empty seat at the table. Dench's husband died in April from Covid-19 complications https://t.co/U1kXSwIYOr
